%N A221446 T(n,k) = number of n X k binary arrays with every 0 a horizontal or antidiagonal neighbor to some 1, n >= 1, k >= 1, read by antidiagonals.
%C A221446 Original definition: T(n,k) = Hilltop maps: number of n X k binary arrays indicating the locations of corresponding elements not exceeded by any horizontal or antidiagonal neighbor in a random 0..1 n X k array.
%C A221446 Number of dominating sets in an n X k grid graph with edges connecting horizontally or antidiagonally adjacent vertices. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 14 2026
